This is all from my own experience. Nothing/A bit/All of the following may apply to you. Insults are not meant to be personal.<br>
<br>
Let's face it...<br>
<br>
Until the Changes Matt has promised go live, bm's and mercs (bm in the following to make it readable) have nothing to offer to their groups.<br>
<br>
We have no anytime stun (leaving the 42 shield bm out of this), we have lousy damage, we have no good class defining abilities...<br>
<br>
Now, let's have a look at those still playing a bm...<br>
<br>
They were once upon a time charmed by the impression of a light armored, dual wielding, fast hitting, insane damage dealing tank mythic promised us.<br>
<br>
-Here a good number deleted their bm-<br>
<br>
They could not be discouraged by the PvE groups who could not understand that bm rocks with their evade. They could not be discouraged by all the &quot;We are gimped, fix us&quot; posts everywhere. They thought they could do better.<br>
<br>
- Another portion of bm quitted playing here nonetheless-<br>
<br>
Finally, they dinged 50 and headed out to do some real RvR. Nobody wanted them in their groups, because they did not offer anything unique...<br>
<br>
- Here we see alot of bm quitting their class-<br>
<br>
Those that knew how to overcome obstacles, and as a bm, you grow up like this, we started to make our own groups.<br>
<br>
Now we were the group leaders, asking/telling peeps that we need them, organizing group/guild/alliance/keep/relic raids. Now we know more than alot of others...<br>
<br>
If they fix our damage, then we are unstoppable indeed... Because we achieved so many other skills others never had to train, we will be<br>
<br>
Teh uba ro&gt; <p>==================<br>
